  "body": "* See https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/4487\r\n\r\nIt may be best to have a boolean flag for enabling/disabling the persistent network id. (eg: `--network.persistId`)\r\nShould also handle loading a corrupt enr.\r\n\r\nBefore #4487, if the enr was not readable, we would recreate the enr (starting from a 0 sequence number). This probably resulted in part of the discv5 network ignoring the new enr. Suggestion to reset the nonce as unix time instead of 0.\r\n",
